a <br>try.  This is HardCore EverQuest.  This is real RolePlaying<br>where the deities you chose are a matter of life and death.<br><br>This is the only server in Everquest that has real zone<br>control.  It is the only server in all of EverQuest that<br>has a point system where your name can be in lights at<br>the end of the day on Sony's web site.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/stats/sz_summary.jsp">everquest.station.sony.co...ummary.jsp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>It is one of the only servers that every night has player<br>created dynamic events like no other. Guildwars that<br>cross many zones. Evils trying to stop goods from getting<br>their cleric Epics. No cross teaming. Very little twinking.<br>And a place where reputation matters because you only have<br>one character per account. <br><br>This server is the place where real role-playing occurs,<br>there is no grouping or guilding between teams, only war,<br>competition and fun. Every night is a GM event night<br>because the players create it. Just running through a zone<br>can be an adventure when in enemy territory.  Going AFK is<br>a dangerous thing, the unexpected can happen, unlike regular<br>EQ.<br><br>Are you bored of 6 hour dragon raids where one person<br>gets something which only increases their STR by 4 points?<br>Why not go on a server where you can make your own fun<br>by raiding into enemy lands and killing for passion or<br>for platinum?  On Sullon Zek, you will have to create<br>a completely different set of gear for resists against players,<br>it adds a completely different dimension to game play beyond<br>what typical EverQuest can offer.  You can make your own<br>Legends there and you don't need a special 40 dollar server.<br><br>Every zone has the possibility of an Uber encounter when<br>enemies raid the lands. And the mobs that attack are real<br>people with smarts and strategy that no AI could ever compete<br>with.   Camps are rarely boring when at any moment enemy's<br>could come out of the woodwork and challenge your group<br>to battle.   You will not be able to level up in the<br>same 3 or 4 zones you are used to, you will have to move<br>and learn new places, new things, new techniques to get<br>around the team zone control.<br><br><br>If you want it easy go on the evil team, they own most of Kunark and<br>level easily without disturbances usually, they are also the largest<br>team. If you want it hard but not impossible go on the neutral team.  <br>If you want the highest challenge of all, go on the good team<br>they are the smallest team but hardy players, every one. Read up<br>on the rules carefully and choose a class carefully.<br><br>Try it, you'll like it, it is like a whole new Everquest.<br><br>All for the regular EQ price, you can make your own Legend there.<br><br>Sullon Zek Deity Teams EverQuest Server. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukaio2k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaio2k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/22/02 10:44:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> /cheer <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showPrevMessage?topicID=43.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showNextMessage?topicID=43.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~